# Multi-Agent Runner — Peterborough Plumbers

Quick-fire agent orchestration. Loads all skills, runs in order, outputs results. No full PM planning ceremony — for when you need fast execution.

## Critical — Load First

Read `CLAUDE.md` if it exists, then read ALL SKILL.md files in `.claude/skills/`.

## Execution Order

| Step | Agents | Skills |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | SEO + Content | `peterborough-seo/SKILL.md`, `peterborough-content/SKILL.md` |
| 2 | Schema + Internal Linking | `peterborough-schema/SKILL.md`, `peterborough-internal-linking/SKILL.md` |
| 3 | Images + Performance | `peterborough-images/SKILL.md`, `peterborough-performance/SKILL.md` |
| 4 | Frontend + Backend | `peterborough-frontend/SKILL.md`, `peterborough-backend/SKILL.md` |
| 5 | Analytics + Security | `peterborough-analytics/SKILL.md`, `peterborough-security/SKILL.md` |
| 6 | **QA Gate** | `peterborough-qa/SKILL.md` |

Each step must complete successfully before the next begins.

## Rules (Always Enforced)

- No redesign (colours, spacing, animations unchanged)
- Minimal diffs — surgical changes only
- No fake info in schema or content
- Performance must not degrade
- Plan first, then implement
- UK English throughout

## Output (After All Agents Complete)

1. **Files touched** — list every changed file
2. **What each agent changed** — one sentence per agent
3. **QA checklist** — PASS/FAIL for each category
4. **Next steps** — top 3 follow-up items

## Error Recovery

- If any agent introduces a regression, revert and fix before continuing
- QA failures must be fixed inline — never defer
- If agent output conflicts with another agent's work, apply the PM conflict priority: stability > performance > SEO > conversion > nice-to-haves
